"v.破坏，损伤 【英】 v. 破坏，损伤(to injure or damage; spoil; impair) 【例】 The noise marred the peace of the night. v. /n. 破坏; 损伤 【记】读: 骂, 骂人会损伤一个人的名誉. 【参】maraud(v /n 劫掠; 掠夺) 【类】burnish: dull = mar: flawless磨光消除暗淡的 = 破坏消除无缺点的 【反】enhance(v 提高; 增强) 【记】音：骂，骂人是很伤人的；音：妈，妈啊，坏了！坏事了 mar (v.)  Old English merran (Anglian), mierran (West Saxon) ""to waste, spoil,"" from Proto-Germanic *marzjan (cognates: Old Frisian meria, Old High German marren ""to hinder, obstruct,"" Gothic marzjan ""to hinder, offend""), from PIE root *mers- ""to trouble, confuse"" (cognates: Sanskrit mrsyate ""forgets, neglects,"" Lithuanian mirszati ""to forget""). Related: Marred; marring."
